Welcome!

Im Hun, my hometown is Busan in South Korea.

I am currently pursuing a Ph.D.program of statistics at Columbia University. I earned my M.S. in biostatistics from Columbia University and B.S. in statistics from University of California, Davis.

I am interested in pursuing my career in research! My research and academic interests lie at the intersection of survey weighting, Bayesian inference, bootstrap theory and resampling, and causal inference.

I am an inquisitive person motivated by faith, hope, love, and insight. I am also interested in soccer, baseball, cooking, mathematics, the books of Fyodor Dostoyevsky, and the books of the Bible.
